    rdau:P61101 "<a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alec_Robertson_(music_critic)'>Wikipedia</a>, katsottu 8.4.2026 (Alec Robertson, MBE (3 June 1892, Southsea – 18 January 1982, Midhurst) was a British writer, broadcaster and music critic. He wrote music criticism for Gramophone for more than 50 years, beginning with the magazine's very first issue in 1923. He later served as that magazine's music editor from 1952 to 1972. Ho joined the Gramophone Department of the BBC in 1940, and worked as producer of music talks on the Home and Third programmes, retiring from the BBC in 1952.)"@fi,
        "<a href='https://www.oxfordmusiconline.com/grovemusic/view/10.1093/gmo/9781561592630.001.0001/omo-9781561592630-e-0000023583'>Grove music online</a>, katsottu 8.4.2026 (Robertson, Alec (Alexander) (Thomas Parke) (b Southsea, June 3, 1892; d Midhurst, Jan 18, 1982). English writer on music. )"@fi ;
